        <Document ID="15A95207-E0DD-4D74-BFA3-3ACF9ECDBA3E">
            <Title>Tell me</Title>
            <Text>“Aliens, huh?” You chuckle, goading him. “Did they have tentacles?”

Iverson hangs his head, as far as helmet will let him. A drop of sweat plops onto the faceplate. “I didn’t…” he starts, then stops and takes a deep breath. “I don’t know. I only saw…” 

He holds up one hand, and you can hear him huffing and puffing. Despite the circulators in his helmet, his faceplate begins to fog. 

&gt; Try and talk some sense to him.
&gt; Tell him to show you.</Text>
